Axis Bank Ltd.,  Indiaâ€™s fourth-
largest lender by market value, hired five banks to sell $500
million of dollar-denominated bonds, according to a person
familiar with the matter.  Bank of America Merrill Lynch, Citigroup Inc., Deutsche
Bank AG, JPMorgan Chase & Co. and Royal Bank of Scotland Group
Plc will help Mumbai-based Axis sell notes with maturities of as
much as 5 1/2 years, the person said, asking not to be
identified as the details are private.  Meetings with investors will start on Oct. 21 in Singapore
and New York, then moving to Hong Kong and Boston before
finishing in London and Los Angeles on Oct. 25, another person
